radiographic_examinations.findings: The imaged lung bases are clear. The heart is unremarkable. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are normal. Kidneys enhance symmetrically and excrete contrast promptly without hydronephrosis or worrisome renal lesion. The abdominal aorta is normal in course and caliber with widely patent major branches. No retroperitoneal lymphadenopathy. The stomach is decompressed. Duodenum is normal. Loops of small bowel demonstrate no signs of ileus or obstruction. The appendix is visualized, dilated with thickened wall and fluid-filled with surrounding fat stranding. No evidence of acute complication, free air or extraluminal fluid collection. Trace free pelvic fluid is noted. The colon is unremarkable. Distal ureters appear normal. Urinary bladder appears distended and unremarkable. No worrisome lytic or blastic osseous lesion. Transitional anatomy at the lumbosacral junction is noted with partial lumbarization of S1.
